 only a change in perception-recognizing the existence of the wisdom of love per se-but also the realization that this wisdom is the very foundation of religious wisdom as a whole, rather than a peripheral branch of it. All love derives from a single source: love between man and woman. It is from this source that all other manifestations of love, such as love of God, love of wisdom, and love of one's fellow, draw their meaning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aLovexReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aSex in rabbinical literature. 0aSexxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aSermoneta-Gertel, Shmuel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618110985423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618110985.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6  ASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG